# Enforce LF line endings in the working tree for files that Prettier
# (and other LF-default tooling) formats. Prettier 3's default
# `endOfLine: "lf"` otherwise flags Windows checkouts as mis-formatted
# while CI (Linux) sees the files as fine — a difference that silently
# blocks local pre-commit hooks.
*.ts text eol=lf
*.tsx text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.jsx text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.dart text eol=lf

# Windows-native scripts should keep CRLF regardless of platform.
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
